sql:
SELECT last_valuation, last_valuation_date
FROM portfolio_instruments
WHERE portfolio_instrument_id = 1;

SELECT instrument_id, added_date
FROM watchlist_instruments
WHERE alert_triggered = 0;

SELECT ticker
FROM financial_instruments
WHERE market_cap = (SELECT MAX(market_cap) FROM financial_instruments);

external_knowledge:
- "Giants in the financial world" refers to financial instruments with the highest market capitalization; 
- "Top 5" refers to the instruments with the highest market capitalization, as ranked by the query; 
- "Average closing prices over the past month" refers to the average closing price of each instrument over the past 30 days, as calculated by the query; 
- "Latest news headlines" refers to the title of the latest news article for each instrument, as retrieved by the query.

sql:
SELECT MAX(last_valuation_date) AS latest_valuation_date
FROM portfolio_instruments
WHERE portfolio_id = 0;

SELECT MAX(timestamp) AS most_recent_timestamp
FROM real_time_prices
WHERE instrument_id = 1;
